The paper deals with the complexity of systems of sets defined by curve similarity metrics, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of sampling bounds and analysis of set systems also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves deriving upper and lower bounds, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of similarity metrics and analysis of curves could also be relevant to information retrieval and search engines (cs.SI).
